        <p class="lead">
          bearerCORE&#8482; is a protocol-grade <strong>CBDC</strong> infrastructure that enables African
          central banks to issue, validate, and settle sovereign digital currency across all 54 corridors
          of the African Union &mdash; without requiring recipients to hold a bank account.
        </p>

        <p>
          Modelled on the physical cash metaphor &mdash; where possession equals ownership &mdash; bearerCORE&#8482;
          introduces the <strong>CVIB</strong> (Cryptographic Visual Image Banknote): a cryptographically signed
          digital banknote minted by a central bank, delivered as <strong>Digital Money Bundles</strong>
