  <h1>The bearerCORE&#8482; Protocol</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    bearerCORE&#8482; introduces a new class of digital monetary instrument: the
    <strong>CVIB</strong> (Cryptographic Visual Image Banknote) &mdash; a cryptographically authenticated
    digital banknote issued exclusively by a licensed central bank, delivered to commercial
    banks as <strong>Digital Money Bundles</strong>.
  </p>

  <p>
    A CVIB is a PNG image file. Like a physical banknote, it carries denomination, issuer
    identity, serial number, and security features &mdash; embedded in the file itself using
    cryptographic primitives rather than ink and paper. The central bank&#8217;s Ed25519 private
    key signs every CVIB at the moment of minting. No entity other than the issuing central
    bank can produce a valid CBDC unit.
  </p>

  <h2>Three-Layer Architecture</h2>

