  <h2>Financial Inclusion by Design</h2>

  <p>
    Because CVIBs are bearer instruments &mdash; value in the file, not in an account &mdash; they
    require no bank account, no credit history, and no KYC at the point of receipt. A
    smallholder farmer in rural Uganda can receive a Digital Money Bundle from a buyer in
    Nairobi as easily as receiving a photograph.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>No account required:</strong> CVIB files are held in local storage, not custodied by a bank</li>
    <li><strong>Offline capable:</strong> CVIBs can be stored and transferred without internet connectivity</li>
    <li><strong>Mobile first:</strong> Cash Codes enable instant verification of any CVIB on any smartphone camera</li>
    <li><strong>Sovereign backed:</strong> Each CVIB is a direct CBDC liability of the issuing central bank &mdash; not a private stablecoin</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="callout">
